{
  "stem": "3964.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And as conditions in Stutthof continued to get worse and worse and worse, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I found out that my sister was working again in a army clothing depot, where they were separating clothing.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "It was very cold in the winter of '44-- '43-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] no, winter of '44, '45 in Stutthof.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And since my sister was working in this army depot, she was able to steal some clothes and was able to get some clothes to myself and my father.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Clothes, of course, didn't do me much good anymore, because I was-- all of a sudden got sick, came down with typhoid and typhus fever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And there was no cure for it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "There were no doctors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The only thing that was available to us [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] were some delousing pills, which the Germans issued to us hopefully not to spread the disease any further.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And what it was was a-- I can still see it in front of my eyes-- was two yellow pills we were given.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Dissolve it in water, soak your clothes in them, and then put your wet clothes on, wintertime.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] The dehydration of the water through your body's warms-- warmth was supposed to kill the lice and the gnats, which are the eggs the lice were laying in-- in your clothes.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "But that was just a pipe dream, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Maybe it did do some good, but as a whole it didn't.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "I deteriorated really, really quick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And I was in bad-- in really bad condition, delirious, high fever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And every day they would go through the barracks, pull people out of barracks to march them to [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
